WEBVTT

00:01.102 --> 00:03.202
<i> Previously on "nashville"...</i>

00:03.204 --> 00:04.679
Scarlett:
There always<i> is</i> something

00:04.680 --> 00:06.155
Just under the surface
with me and gunnar.

00:06.156 --> 00:07.631
That's just where
it's got to stay.

00:07.632 --> 00:09.107
I'd like you to come back
to wheelin' dealin' records,

00:09.110 --> 00:10.309
You bet.

00:10.311 --> 00:12.144
I'm going on tour
with layla.

00:12.146 --> 00:13.312
Riff may not make it.

00:13.314 --> 00:15.014
He's looking for
a replacement, right?

00:15.016 --> 00:18.050
Welcome back to my tour
miss juliette barnes!

00:18.052 --> 00:20.019
She's 16 years old!

00:20.021 --> 00:21.153
Deacon:
I did the right thing.

00:21.155 --> 00:22.221
If you did
the right thing,

00:22.223 --> 00:23.655
Why you suppose
maddie ran away?

00:23.657 --> 00:25.224
You're trying to keep me
from my career.

00:25.226 --> 00:27.126
Sony wanted me,
and so did edgehill.

00:27.128 --> 00:29.094
I'm emancipating from you.

00:30.064 --> 00:31.397
[ camera shutter clicks ]

00:31.399 --> 00:32.464
All right,
nice big smile.

00:32.466 --> 00:33.499
[ camera shutter clicking ]

00:33.501 --> 00:34.733
Such a beautiful home
you two have.

00:34.735 --> 00:36.235
-Thank you.
-Yeah, it's really more hers.

00:36.237 --> 00:37.737
I just moved in
a little bit ago.

00:37.738 --> 00:39.238
Well, it's where
you're raising your family,

00:39.240 --> 00:41.240
And that's what<i> southern living</i>
readers want to peek into --

00:41.242 --> 00:43.275
The amazing life
of rayna jaymes.

00:43.277 --> 00:44.543
[ chuckles ]

00:44.545 --> 00:45.677
Sid, we want
to get the kids in this?

00:45.679 --> 00:46.812
Yeah, that'd be great.

00:46.814 --> 00:48.414
I'm sorry.

00:48.416 --> 00:50.382
No, our publicist
talked to you guys about this.

00:50.384 --> 00:52.451
It's just gonna be
rayna and deacon today.

00:52.453 --> 00:55.320
Well, maybe we could get some
shots at the benefit tomorrow?

00:55.322 --> 00:57.356
Well, let's...Play it by ear.
You guys done in here?

00:57.358 --> 00:58.424
You have what you need?
-Yeah, we're good.

00:58.426 --> 00:59.758
Okay, great.
Now, let's --

00:59.760 --> 01:01.160
Let's head to the kitchen.
Follow me.

01:01.162 --> 01:02.445
-Okay.
-All right.

01:02.446 --> 01:03.729
The kitchen's really
the heart of this home,

01:03.731 --> 01:04.830
And I've been lucky enough
to enjoy

01:04.832 --> 01:06.165
A lot
of great family dinners here.

01:06.167 --> 01:07.400
Photographer:
Oh, and it's so sunny!

01:07.401 --> 01:08.634
Baby, I can't take
all this posing,

01:08.636 --> 01:11.303
All this acting like
everything's fine and dandy,

01:11.305 --> 01:13.539
Ducking and dodging around
what's going on with the girls.

01:13.541 --> 01:16.141
This is just...

01:16.143 --> 01:18.277
We got to make
some kind of damn move here.

01:18.279 --> 01:21.080
I just don't think
the move is ours to make.

01:22.750 --> 01:24.083
I think we're just...

01:24.085 --> 01:25.617
[ sighs ]

01:25.619 --> 01:28.353
...Gonna have to hold tight
and...

01:28.355 --> 01:30.622
Hope she comes to
her senses.

01:30.624 --> 01:31.623
[ cheers and applause ]

01:31.625 --> 01:33.392
-You look amazing.
-Thank you.

01:33.394 --> 01:36.328
Nervous? First time
back in front of an arena crowd.

01:36.330 --> 01:39.398
Oh, it's easy to get
20,000 people to love you.

01:39.400 --> 01:40.766
Thank you.

01:43.204 --> 01:45.704
Thank you, raleigh!

01:45.706 --> 01:48.207
[ "one place too long" plays ]

01:50.311 --> 01:54.847
Oh, I'm so excited to be
back on tour with luke wheeler.

01:54.849 --> 01:58.383
Let's pick up
where we left off, shall we?

01:58.385 --> 02:00.719
[ cheers and applause ]

02:03.757 --> 02:06.592
¶ life is like a poplar tree ¶

02:06.594 --> 02:09.361
¶ some are the roots,
some are the leaves ¶

02:09.363 --> 02:12.197
¶ stayin' put
ain't stuck with me ¶

02:12.199 --> 02:14.600
¶ I slip out
while the city sleeps ¶

02:14.602 --> 02:16.168
¶ I'm gone ¶

02:16.170 --> 02:18.203
¶ gone, gone, gone ¶

02:19.640 --> 02:24.176
¶ well, I'm gone, gone, gone ¶

02:25.713 --> 02:30.916
¶ soon as I get there,
I've already left ¶

02:30.918 --> 02:36.788
¶ I get high on every mile,
wearin' out the treads ¶

02:36.790 --> 02:42.227
¶ kinda like the radio
keeps playin' different songs ¶

02:42.229 --> 02:47.533
¶ I can't stay in one place
too long ¶

02:47.535 --> 02:52.704
¶ no, I can't
stay in one place too long ¶

02:52.706 --> 02:55.941
[ crowd cheering ]

02:55.943 --> 02:59.178
¶ change of pace,
change of scene ¶

02:59.180 --> 03:01.914
¶ might as well
change everything ¶

03:01.916 --> 03:04.750
¶ call it runnin',
call it movin' on ¶

03:04.752 --> 03:06.752
Juliette's
back in the saddle.

03:06.754 --> 03:08.487
Yep.
Crowd seems to love her.

03:08.489 --> 03:09.888
[ sighs ]

03:09.890 --> 03:11.690
More importantly,
nobody's asking for a refund.

03:11.692 --> 03:13.993
[ chuckling ] yeah.

03:13.994 --> 03:16.295
I'm just glad the press bought
riff leaving for health reasons,

03:16.297 --> 03:18.330
Especially
for his family's sake.

03:18.332 --> 03:20.199
And yours.

03:20.201 --> 03:22.401
Last question you want to hear
on national television is

03:22.403 --> 03:23.802
"hey, luke,
how's your former tour mate

03:23.804 --> 03:25.571
Handling
his sex addiction?"

03:25.573 --> 03:27.606
[ laughs ] yeah, well,
I'm happy to dodge that bullet.

03:27.608 --> 03:29.474
Cheers.
-Cheers.

03:29.476 --> 03:32.611
So, how are things coming along
with will's showcase?

03:32.613 --> 03:36.381
No point in launching an album
if we don't get solid airplay.

03:36.383 --> 03:38.350
Invited 50
of the top programmers.

03:38.352 --> 03:40.219
Most of whom I have
great relationships with.

03:40.221 --> 03:42.354
Still,
it's a hill to climb.

03:42.356 --> 03:44.156
You know
there's never been

03:44.157 --> 03:45.957
An openly gay artist
on country radio.

03:45.960 --> 03:47.926
Yeah, which is why
it's time to climb it.

03:56.670 --> 03:58.303
-[ gasps ]
-hey.

03:58.305 --> 03:59.955
[ chuckling ]
you scared the crap out of me.

03:59.956 --> 04:01.606
Sorry. I was -- I was
just putting cadence down.

04:01.609 --> 04:03.375
-Oh, I'm sorry.
-No, no, no. It's fine.

04:04.712 --> 04:06.378
What are you, uh,
what are you doing here?

04:06.380 --> 04:07.980
Isn't the show still on?

04:07.982 --> 04:10.149
Am I a horrible person
for wishing

04:10.150 --> 04:12.317
That juliette would just
be a little wobbly
her first night back?

04:12.319 --> 04:14.386
"horrible" isn't the word
I'd use to describe you at all.

04:14.388 --> 04:17.489
Right. Brilliant,
captivating, mysterious.

04:17.491 --> 04:18.523
All of the above.

04:18.525 --> 04:19.958
[ both chuckle ]

04:21.428 --> 04:22.694
Why didn't<i> you</i>
stay for the show?

04:22.696 --> 04:24.730
I've seen it before.

04:24.732 --> 04:26.749
And cadence was tired.

04:26.750 --> 04:28.767
Plus, I had some ideas
for the track we're working on,

04:28.769 --> 04:30.469
Wanted to get them down
before I forget.

04:30.471 --> 04:32.471
Hm.

04:32.473 --> 04:33.972
You want to work on them
with me?

04:33.974 --> 04:35.574
Sure. Why not?

04:35.576 --> 04:37.009
Okay.

04:42.683 --> 04:44.983
Just made popcorn.
Want some?

04:44.985 --> 04:46.585
Nope. Working.

04:46.587 --> 04:47.686
[ cellphone rings ]

04:47.688 --> 04:48.887
Okay.

04:48.889 --> 04:50.889
Hey, it's will.

04:50.891 --> 04:51.690
Dude.

04:51.692 --> 04:53.025
You're on the radio!

04:53.027 --> 04:54.526
We're on the radio
in nashville!

04:54.528 --> 04:55.927
[ chuckles ]

04:55.929 --> 04:57.596
Yeah, you'll probably
be on the charts

04:57.598 --> 04:58.697
By the end of the month.

04:58.699 --> 05:00.232
God knows we're trying,
man.

05:00.234 --> 05:02.768
Wall-to-wall interviews
in like eight different cities.

05:02.770 --> 05:03.568
[ chuckles ]

05:03.570 --> 05:04.770
Ooh! And guess what.

05:04.772 --> 05:06.738
<i> Rolling stone country</i>
called.

05:06.740 --> 05:08.807
We're sitting down with them
day after tomorrow.

05:08.809 --> 05:10.976
It's nice to have a label head
on your side, isn't it?

05:10.978 --> 05:12.678
Luke's got me
playing a showcase

05:12.680 --> 05:15.647
For like 50 programmers
tomorrow.

05:15.649 --> 05:18.016
Hey, put scarlett on the phone.
Let me say hi to her.

05:18.018 --> 05:21.720
I<i> would,</i> but she seems to not be
speaking to me at the moment.

05:21.722 --> 05:22.855
Oh, what'd you do now?

05:22.856 --> 05:23.989
Why do you assume
<i> I</i> did something?

05:23.991 --> 05:25.724
Because you probably did.

05:28.362 --> 05:32.030
So, did you talk to avery
about flying with me on the jet

05:32.032 --> 05:34.399
Instead of riding
on that cramped tour bus?

05:34.401 --> 05:36.935
Yeah, he appreciates the offer,
but he politely declined.

05:36.937 --> 05:38.937
He'd rather drive nine hours
in a bus

05:38.939 --> 05:40.605
Than fly one hour
with me?

05:40.607 --> 05:41.940
Apparently so.

05:43.944 --> 05:45.811
Is something going on
between him and layla?

05:45.813 --> 05:47.612
Yes --
they're recording an album.

05:47.614 --> 05:49.014
There's a mobile studio
on her bus.

05:49.016 --> 05:50.649
Avery's just trying
to maximize their work time.

05:50.651 --> 05:52.984
Mm-hmm.

05:52.986 --> 05:56.455
Juliette,
the only thing going on

05:56.457 --> 05:59.391
Between avery and layla
is her music.

05:59.393 --> 06:01.793
Wait till you hear it
with your vocals doubled.

06:01.795 --> 06:03.895
Here. Take a listen.

06:03.897 --> 06:06.998
¶ they tricked you into thinkin'
both your wings are clipped ¶

06:07.000 --> 06:08.867
¶ and you ain't ever
seein' the sky ¶

06:08.869 --> 06:11.002
Wow.

06:11.004 --> 06:12.471
¶ if you could see
what I see ¶

06:12.473 --> 06:13.438
Thank you.

06:13.440 --> 06:14.806
¶ maybe then you'd believe ¶

06:14.808 --> 06:16.942
¶ the light you got
will always rise ¶

06:16.944 --> 06:19.544
I wish there was
a more powerful word
for "beautiful."

06:19.546 --> 06:21.513
¶ ...Big world outside ¶

06:21.515 --> 06:22.714
Me too.

06:22.716 --> 06:26.518
¶ oh, ain't it time you fly? ¶

06:26.520 --> 06:30.822
¶ life, well,
it don't have to hurt ¶

06:33.660 --> 06:36.161
¶ if you could see
what I see ¶

06:36.163 --> 06:37.129
[ amplified ]
¶ maybe then you'd believe ¶

06:37.131 --> 06:38.797
[ both chuckle, music stops ]

06:38.799 --> 06:40.866
[ cadence crying ]

06:40.868 --> 06:42.434
[ sighs ]

06:44.772 --> 06:47.572
I should really get cadence
back to the hotel.

06:47.574 --> 06:49.040
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

06:54.181 --> 06:56.515
-Great to meet you, deacon.
-My pleasure.

06:56.517 --> 06:58.583
Well, thanks for opening up
your home to<i> southern living.</i>

06:58.585 --> 07:00.352
It's gonna be a great
50th anniversary issue

07:00.354 --> 07:01.553
With you on the cover.

07:01.555 --> 07:03.422
Oh, well, I hope so.
[ chuckles ]

07:03.424 --> 07:05.123
So, our photographer will be
at the ryman tomorrow night

07:05.125 --> 07:07.025
To grab some candids
of the family.

07:07.027 --> 07:09.060
Uh...Okay. Uh --

07:09.062 --> 07:11.096
And we'll run everything
past bucky, of course.

07:11.098 --> 07:12.281
Great.
Okay.

07:12.282 --> 07:13.465
All right.
Thank you, sid.

07:13.467 --> 07:15.000
Night, rayna.
Take care.

07:17.204 --> 07:19.070
[ knock on door ]

07:19.072 --> 07:20.138
Yeah?

07:20.140 --> 07:21.606
This is for you,
miss jaymes.

07:21.608 --> 07:22.808
Uh, thank you.

07:29.950 --> 07:31.450
What's going on?
What is it?

07:31.452 --> 07:32.984
[ sighs ]

07:34.788 --> 07:38.657
It's an order to appear in court
on behalf of maddie.

07:38.659 --> 07:40.125
For what?

07:40.127 --> 07:41.526
An emancipation hearing.

07:45.165 --> 07:46.965
What's "emancipation" mean?

07:46.967 --> 07:48.800
Um...

07:50.971 --> 07:54.039
Honey,
your sister wants to...

07:54.041 --> 07:56.007
Wants to live
independently.

07:56.009 --> 07:59.778
Does that mean
she's divorcing us?

07:59.780 --> 08:02.948
¶¶

08:13.026 --> 08:13.625
Thank you.
Here she is.

08:13.626 --> 08:14.225
Hi, rayna.
I'm david mannis.

08:14.228 --> 08:16.628
Nice to meet you.
Thanks for coming.

08:16.630 --> 08:18.663
Sorry to hold you up
a little bit.

08:18.665 --> 08:22.167
It was not easy getting
my daughter daphne down tonight.

08:22.169 --> 08:23.768
I imagine
you're all quite upset.

08:23.770 --> 08:26.872
Yeah, well, they got this thing
to court in 48 hours.

08:26.874 --> 08:28.841
I mean,
how's that even possible?

08:28.842 --> 08:30.809
Well, in juvenile matters, the
court tends to be expeditious.

08:30.811 --> 08:31.977
And what kind of court
is it?

08:31.979 --> 08:33.778
I mean, is it

08:33.780 --> 08:35.914
Depositions and testimonies --
that kind of --

08:35.916 --> 08:37.682
Yeah, 'cause if it is, please
get me on the stand, all right?

08:37.684 --> 08:38.817
'cause I want
to talk to this judge.

08:38.819 --> 08:40.252
I want to tell him
about cash.

08:40.254 --> 08:41.920
She's like a snake
leading her away.

08:41.922 --> 08:44.155
Actually, you're not listed
in the action.

08:44.157 --> 08:45.891
I'm sorry. What?

08:45.893 --> 08:48.260
Teddy conrad is still
maddie's legal parent.

08:48.262 --> 08:50.161
Now, I recognize, of course,
that he's in prison,

08:50.163 --> 08:51.796
But from a legal standpoint,
that's irrelevant.

08:51.798 --> 08:53.732
Look, I'm her biological father,
all right?

08:53.734 --> 08:55.667
So don't tell me
I don't have any rights here.

08:55.669 --> 08:58.937
You<i> would,</i> but establishing that
legally would take months.

08:58.939 --> 09:00.472
We go to court
in two days.

09:00.474 --> 09:02.157
[ exhales sharply ]

09:02.158 --> 09:03.841
Can we just
<i> talk</i> to maddie?

09:03.844 --> 09:06.211
We can ask the judge to order
mediation at the hearing.

09:06.213 --> 09:07.546
I'm not talking
about mediation.

09:07.548 --> 09:09.014
I'm just talking about

09:09.016 --> 09:11.283
Having a conversation
with our daughter.

09:11.285 --> 09:13.184
I've checked
with maddie's counsel.

09:13.186 --> 09:15.120
They're unwilling
to wait.

09:15.122 --> 09:17.188
We have no choice
but to prepare you

09:17.190 --> 09:18.957
And your ex-husband
as codefendants.

09:22.796 --> 09:24.796
Tara: The edgehill deal,
sony offer,

09:24.798 --> 09:26.565
Current label interest --

09:26.567 --> 09:28.333
All of it shows the court
you can support yourself.

09:28.335 --> 09:29.834
And you'll make sure
that they know

09:29.836 --> 09:31.603
That her mom
blocked all those offers

09:31.605 --> 09:33.939
In favor of a bogus deal
at highway 65?

09:33.941 --> 09:36.041
It'll certainly be
our argument.

09:36.043 --> 09:37.175
What are we doing
about school?

09:37.177 --> 09:39.210
Um, I signed up
for the proficiency exam

09:39.212 --> 09:41.212
So I can
get my diploma early.

09:41.214 --> 09:42.747
Excellent.
And the plan from there?

09:42.749 --> 09:44.115
Pursue a career in music.

09:45.319 --> 09:47.886
My sister keeps texting me,
and I haven't responded.

09:47.888 --> 09:49.087
Is it okay
if I text her back now?

09:49.089 --> 09:50.855
Probably best not to.

09:50.857 --> 09:52.891
For all we know,
your parents are using her phone

09:52.893 --> 09:54.025
To talk you out of this.

09:54.027 --> 09:55.160
I hadn't even
thought about that.

09:55.162 --> 09:56.962
Okay, so when
can I contact her, then?

09:56.964 --> 09:58.697
Until you're emancipated,

09:58.699 --> 10:00.932
I'd avoid contact
with<i> anyone</i> in that household.

10:06.607 --> 10:07.906
Hey.

10:07.908 --> 10:09.107
Hey.

10:09.109 --> 10:11.042
Morning.

10:11.044 --> 10:12.711
[ sighs ]

10:12.713 --> 10:15.614
Listen,
I-I've been up all night.

10:15.616 --> 10:16.815
Can I go first?

10:16.817 --> 10:18.617
I just --
I really need to say this.

10:18.619 --> 10:19.618
[ sighs ]

10:19.620 --> 10:22.721
I like you, avery.

10:22.723 --> 10:25.757
I like making music with you
onstage and in the studio,

10:25.759 --> 10:27.325
And I like talking t--

10:27.327 --> 10:28.960
Layla...

10:28.962 --> 10:30.662
I like you, too.

10:31.765 --> 10:33.898
"it's not you, it's me,"
right?

10:33.900 --> 10:36.267
It's complicated
with cadence.

10:36.269 --> 10:37.369
And juliette.

10:38.705 --> 10:42.841
Having my ex unexpectedly
join the tour,

10:42.843 --> 10:45.744
It's -- it's a lot
to deal with,

10:45.746 --> 10:48.346
And I just think
that it's best

10:48.348 --> 10:50.849
If we keep things
the way they are between us.

10:52.285 --> 10:53.918
Okay, then.

10:53.920 --> 10:55.820
-Layla, listen, I-I didn't --
-no, it's okay.

10:55.822 --> 10:59.190
You know, it's just --
it's too bad.

10:59.192 --> 11:01.292
'cause we really do
have something.

11:12.139 --> 11:14.039
[ elevator bell dings ]

11:15.976 --> 11:17.942
Hey! Scarlett,
h-hold the elevator.

11:26.987 --> 11:27.986
[ elevator whirring ]

11:27.988 --> 11:29.754
-What the hell was that?
-What?

11:29.756 --> 11:31.189
Seriously?
You've been ignoring me

11:31.191 --> 11:32.457
And shooting me dirty looks
ever since we left dallas.

11:32.459 --> 11:33.909
W-what'd I do?

11:33.910 --> 11:35.360
Maybe we've just been
joined at the hip for four days

11:35.362 --> 11:36.995
And I need
some space from you.

11:36.997 --> 11:38.830
[ elevator clanks,
whirring stops ]

11:39.700 --> 11:40.465
What just happened?

11:40.467 --> 11:42.033
I don't know.

11:42.035 --> 11:43.835
[ button tapping ]

11:43.837 --> 11:45.437
Well, that's not good.

11:47.040 --> 11:49.407
Uh,
I think we're stuck.

11:49.409 --> 11:50.742
[ chuckles ]

11:51.778 --> 11:53.878
Help!!

11:53.880 --> 11:55.847
So,
how'd it come to this?

11:55.849 --> 11:57.415
Well...
It's complicated.

11:57.417 --> 11:59.150
There was this young woman
that we brought in

11:59.152 --> 12:01.419
To mentor maddie
in songwriting,

12:01.421 --> 12:03.488
And she just ended up
being a terrible influence

12:03.490 --> 12:08.126
And encouraged her to lie
and go play at clubs

12:08.128 --> 12:09.260
And now run away.

12:09.262 --> 12:11.613
Well,
who is this person?

12:11.614 --> 12:13.965
She's the daughter
of deacon's business partner.

12:13.967 --> 12:15.200
Oh.

12:15.202 --> 12:16.768
So<i> he</i> brought her
into this.

12:16.770 --> 12:18.069
Don't do that.

12:18.071 --> 12:19.304
Look, there's no way
we could've known

12:19.306 --> 12:20.772
That she was gonna
be like this.

12:20.774 --> 12:22.273
And, anyway,
that's only part of the problem.

12:22.275 --> 12:24.075
Maddie also found out about

12:24.077 --> 12:26.077
That crazy edgehill deal
you made.

12:29.216 --> 12:30.482
How much
does she know about it?

12:30.484 --> 12:32.517
Just that there<i> was</i> one

12:32.519 --> 12:34.252
And that<i> I</i> kept her
from taking it.

12:34.254 --> 12:35.820
Okay.

12:37.357 --> 12:39.441
What are you asking me
to do?

12:39.442 --> 12:41.526
Well, the lawyer has an
affidavit that you can sign --

12:41.528 --> 12:43.928
Basically
tells the court

12:43.930 --> 12:45.930
That you're in agreement
with me.

12:45.932 --> 12:47.165
Let me
talk to maddie first,

12:47.167 --> 12:48.867
And then I'll let you know
what I think.

12:48.869 --> 12:50.401
When are you gonna
talk to maddie?
Today.

12:50.403 --> 12:51.503
She's coming to the prison
today?

12:51.505 --> 12:53.138
Yeah.

12:53.140 --> 12:54.305
You're just
telling me this<i> now?</i>

12:54.307 --> 12:56.107
Rayna, I heard
your side of the story.

12:56.109 --> 12:57.108
Now I'd like
to hear maddie's.

13:00.547 --> 13:02.147
[ gasps ]
ooh, look.

13:02.149 --> 13:03.948
Cadence, look at that.

13:03.950 --> 13:05.416
That is
a treasure chest.

13:05.418 --> 13:07.452
[ gasps ]
what does she think's inside?

13:08.488 --> 13:09.954
Hi, baby.

13:09.956 --> 13:11.990
What are you
doing here?

13:11.992 --> 13:13.725
I was just on my way
to rehearsal,

13:13.726 --> 13:15.459
And I thought I'd sneak
a "hello" with my baby girl.

13:15.462 --> 13:19.030
No, I mean, what are you
doing<i> here --</i> on this tour?

13:19.032 --> 13:20.265
Avery,
this is where cadence is.

13:20.267 --> 13:22.300
I can't be a mom
if I'm not near my daughter.

13:24.805 --> 13:26.070
I'm sorry.

13:26.072 --> 13:29.107
It just [sighs]
took me by surprise.

13:29.109 --> 13:30.041
That's all.

13:30.043 --> 13:31.442
No,
it was all last-minute.

13:31.444 --> 13:34.245
I'm still trying
to get my set tighter.

13:34.247 --> 13:37.015
Which is why I was hoping
that you'd do me a favor.

13:37.017 --> 13:40.218
How do you feel
about playing "dirt" with me?

13:40.220 --> 13:42.053
Onstage during your set?
Come on.

13:42.055 --> 13:43.388
I still can't find
a guitarist

13:43.390 --> 13:44.923
That can play those riffs
like you can.

13:44.925 --> 13:46.357
Yeah, I-I don't know.

13:47.327 --> 13:49.060
[ chuckles ]

13:49.062 --> 13:51.429
It was glenn's idea,
but I think it's a good one.

13:51.431 --> 13:53.998
I'll let you know.

13:54.000 --> 13:56.000
But we really should
get going.

13:56.002 --> 13:57.502
Say goodbye, cadence.

13:57.504 --> 13:59.504
Mama loves you.

13:59.506 --> 14:00.505
Bye, baby.

14:00.507 --> 14:02.373
[ elevator bell dings ]

14:02.375 --> 14:04.576
Glenn:
Well, with the oscars coming up,
juliette's kind of booked.

14:04.578 --> 14:05.844
I'll get back to you.
[ cellphone clicks ]

14:05.846 --> 14:07.145
-Hey.
-Hey.

14:07.147 --> 14:08.263
I've been trying to reach you
all morning.

14:08.264 --> 14:09.380
[ sighs ]
have you heard from rayna yet

14:09.382 --> 14:10.982
About the rough cut
of the video?

14:10.984 --> 14:12.483
Uh, no. I'll let you know
as soon as I do, though.

14:12.485 --> 14:14.552
Okay. Well, I have some ideas
for my album launch party --

14:14.554 --> 14:16.254
And I-I want to hear them --
I do --

14:16.256 --> 14:18.623
But juliette needs me
at rehearsal, so I got to go.

14:18.625 --> 14:20.391
I'll call you
as soon as I'm done, okay?

14:20.393 --> 14:22.093
-Okay.
-All right.

14:23.163 --> 14:24.863
[ scoffs ]

14:24.865 --> 14:27.465
[ cellphone rings ]

14:27.467 --> 14:30.435
I'm sitting in a prison,
hoping to run into my daughter,

14:30.437 --> 14:33.037
So unless this is about
business, I'm not interested.

14:33.039 --> 14:34.539
Yeah, I know,
but I think

14:34.541 --> 14:36.541
That's why you're gonna want
to call scott borchetta.

14:36.543 --> 14:37.876
Why scott borchetta?

14:37.878 --> 14:40.011
Apparently,
cash called big machine.

14:40.013 --> 14:42.146
She wanted to set up a meeting
with them this afternoon

14:42.148 --> 14:45.049
With maddie to pitch her
as a solo artist.

14:45.051 --> 14:47.151
Scott, of course,
did not take the meeting.

14:47.153 --> 14:49.153
Ask him to call her back
and set the meeting.

14:49.155 --> 14:50.321
Okay?
Okay.

14:50.323 --> 14:51.489
Thanks.

14:51.491 --> 14:53.291
[ cellphone clicks ]

14:55.262 --> 14:57.328
[ sighs ] I got caught
in traffic. We start yet?

14:57.330 --> 14:59.364
-No.
-Why the hell not?

14:59.366 --> 15:02.000
'cause hardly anyone showed.
[ sighs ]

15:02.002 --> 15:04.569
Well, I guess,
we'll, uh, go ahead and do this.

15:04.571 --> 15:06.571
[ clears throat ]

15:14.180 --> 15:15.079
Of course I'd understand
if it were an emergency, pete.

15:15.081 --> 15:16.631
Oh, emergency, my ass.

15:16.632 --> 15:18.182
I guess five programmers
is better than none.

15:18.184 --> 15:20.919
I'm hearing everything from
food poisoning to car trouble.

15:20.921 --> 15:22.320
Aw, bull crap.
They're just too chicken

15:22.322 --> 15:24.122
To put a gay artist
on the radio.

15:24.124 --> 15:25.590
They're scared about
angry listeners calling in,

15:25.592 --> 15:27.325
Backlash, boycotts.

15:27.327 --> 15:30.328
Maybe we just need to roll back,
do a smaller launch.

15:30.330 --> 15:32.964
-We might have to.
-Going smaller ain't the answer.

15:34.134 --> 15:36.034
We got to go bigger.

15:36.036 --> 15:38.136
Yeah. Okay.
Thank you.

15:39.673 --> 15:41.639
There's a blackout --
10 whole blocks.

15:41.641 --> 15:43.124
City's working on it,

15:43.125 --> 15:44.608
But nobody knows when
the power's gonna be back.

15:44.611 --> 15:46.411
Can't they just
pry this stupid door open?

15:46.413 --> 15:47.979
Apparently,
we're in between floors.

15:47.981 --> 15:49.580
We could
go through the top.

15:49.582 --> 15:51.716
Scarlett, it's not
"mission: Impossible," okay?

15:51.718 --> 15:54.585
The hotel says the safest thing
to do is just relax and wait.

15:55.689 --> 15:57.588
I need a drink.

16:03.463 --> 16:05.246
[ sighs ]

16:05.247 --> 16:07.030
Since when do you travel with
a bottle of 18-year-old scotch?

16:07.033 --> 16:08.066
Since I found out
that autumn

16:08.068 --> 16:09.500
Was a lying,
backstabbing cougar.

16:09.502 --> 16:12.070
Wow. Okay, uh [chuckles] you
want to tell me what's going on?

16:12.072 --> 16:13.237
[ scoffs ]
it was supposed to be

16:13.239 --> 16:15.123
A thank-you present
for the spa day,

16:15.124 --> 16:17.008
But then I go up to her room,
and you're walking out of there,

16:17.010 --> 16:18.610
Wiping her lipstick
off your face,

16:18.611 --> 16:20.211
Which means she was just
pretending to be my friend,

16:20.213 --> 16:21.946
Pretending to care about us.
-Scarlett, look --

16:21.947 --> 16:23.680
You can sleep with
whoever you want. I don't care.

16:23.683 --> 16:25.066
But did it
have to be my idol?

16:25.067 --> 16:26.450
You have, like, a list of people
who are important to me

16:26.453 --> 16:27.452
That you're gonna --
-all right, all right.

16:27.454 --> 16:29.187
Scarlett, stop. Stop.

16:29.189 --> 16:30.588
I did not sleep with autumn,
all right?

16:30.590 --> 16:33.224
-Sure.
-Yeah, she made a play for me.

16:33.226 --> 16:34.559
She invited me
to go off with her

16:34.561 --> 16:36.094
And hang out
with james taylor.

16:37.397 --> 16:38.596
You love james taylor.

16:38.598 --> 16:40.765
I know.

16:40.767 --> 16:42.367
But I turned her down.
All right?

16:42.369 --> 16:43.634
'cause I didn't want
to do anything

16:43.636 --> 16:46.104
That could
jeopardize the band.

16:48.608 --> 16:49.640
[ sighs ]

16:49.642 --> 16:50.675
Drink?

16:54.347 --> 16:56.047
[ "willing heart" plays ]

16:56.049 --> 16:58.783
¶ I'm gonna need an anchor ¶

17:01.087 --> 17:03.121
¶ an anchor ¶

17:04.457 --> 17:06.591
[ sighs ]

17:06.593 --> 17:08.493
Ah.

17:08.495 --> 17:11.162
The old
"throw the guitar down" trick.

17:11.164 --> 17:13.231
I tried that one
a few times myself.

17:13.233 --> 17:15.099
Doesn't make it
play any better.

17:16.569 --> 17:18.102
You want to talk
about your sister at all?

17:18.104 --> 17:20.238
Rather learn this song...

17:20.240 --> 17:22.540
Since I'm probably
playing it by myself tonight.

17:22.542 --> 17:24.742
First time
performing solo, huh?

17:24.744 --> 17:27.445
Well,
maybe I can help you.

17:27.447 --> 17:30.481
I don't<i> just</i> throw them,
you know.

17:30.483 --> 17:32.650
I play them sometimes,
too.

17:35.055 --> 17:36.587
<i> Hi. This is glenn goodman.</i>
<i> Sorry I missed your call.</i>

17:36.589 --> 17:38.256
<i> Please leave me a message.</i>
<i> I'll get back to you</i>

17:38.258 --> 17:39.757
<i> As soon as I can. Thanks.</i>
[<i> beep</i> ]

17:39.759 --> 17:42.160
Why are you telling juliette
that I should perform with her?

17:42.162 --> 17:44.195
I need boundaries.

17:44.197 --> 17:46.731
And I'd appreciate it
if you'd help keep those clear.

17:46.733 --> 17:49.333
So as her manager,
please tell juliette

17:49.335 --> 17:53.071
That I will not playing "dirt"
or anything with her.

17:53.073 --> 17:54.439
I'm here for layla.

17:54.441 --> 17:56.258
Thanks.

17:56.259 --> 17:58.076
Thank y'all so much.
Enjoy your night off.

17:58.078 --> 18:00.244
Oh, please tell me
I have nothing else to do.

18:00.246 --> 18:01.512
I want to get to bed
early

18:01.514 --> 18:04.248
So I can get up
for the oscar nominations.

18:04.250 --> 18:05.616
[ sighs ]

18:05.618 --> 18:06.417
What?

18:06.419 --> 18:08.119
What's wrong?

18:08.121 --> 18:10.154
Why would avery think that
I want him performing with you?

18:11.357 --> 18:14.158
Well, I might have told
a little white lie.

18:14.160 --> 18:16.394
I just thought
that if he knew

18:16.396 --> 18:18.129
You were on board,
<i> he</i> would be, too,

18:18.131 --> 18:21.432
And I think that us playing
the song together is the best.

18:21.434 --> 18:23.401
Juliette, listen,
I took you back as a client

18:23.403 --> 18:25.369
Because I thought
that you had changed,

18:25.371 --> 18:27.472
That all this lying
and the manipulation --

18:27.474 --> 18:29.407
Look, I<i> have</i> changed.
I<i> have</i> changed.

18:29.409 --> 18:30.775
I'm sorry. Okay?

18:30.777 --> 18:32.577
It was a stupid move.

18:32.579 --> 18:34.462
I just was hoping

18:34.463 --> 18:36.346
That if we spent time
together, then --

18:36.349 --> 18:38.249
No, no.

18:38.250 --> 18:40.150
If you really want avery to see
how far you've come,

18:40.153 --> 18:43.254
Try being honest with him
instead of lying to him.

18:44.524 --> 18:46.224
[ scoffs ]

18:49.462 --> 18:50.695
[ sighs ]

18:50.697 --> 18:52.163
[ applause ]
hey, robin.

18:52.164 --> 18:53.630
-Oh, it's great to see you!
-Good to see you.

18:53.633 --> 18:54.866
Thanks for having me.
Thank you.

18:54.868 --> 18:56.134
Oh, good to have you
on the show.

18:56.136 --> 18:57.468
Nice to be here
with you good people

18:57.470 --> 18:59.770
And all you folks
watching at home.

18:59.772 --> 19:01.739
How many of them are there
that watch across the country?

19:01.741 --> 19:03.808
-I'd say a few billion or so.
-I think I already knew that.

19:03.810 --> 19:07.411
But, um, so we may have a-a
surprise in store for you today.

19:07.413 --> 19:09.247
That's right, because
originally, we had planned

19:09.249 --> 19:10.414
For<i> you</i> to perform,
but --

19:10.416 --> 19:11.749
But I-I asked robin here

19:11.751 --> 19:14.619
If I could
bring somebody else out instead,

19:14.621 --> 19:15.720
And I did that

19:15.722 --> 19:18.523
Because there's an artist
and an issue

19:18.525 --> 19:20.858
Worth sacrificing my time
on the national stage for.

19:20.860 --> 19:23.628
What you said, my friend,
because you may know him

19:23.630 --> 19:26.531
From having come out publicly
earlier this year.

19:26.533 --> 19:29.901
Please welcome to the stage
mr. Will lexington!

19:29.903 --> 19:30.902
Yay, will!

19:30.904 --> 19:33.638
[ cheers and applause ]

19:35.542 --> 19:36.707
Hi, cash.

19:36.709 --> 19:38.576
What are you doing here?

19:38.578 --> 19:40.245
You mean,
instead of scott borchetta?

19:40.246 --> 19:41.913
He didn't feel like
there was any point
in going to a meeting

19:41.915 --> 19:44.415
With somebody who's already
signed at highway 65.

19:44.417 --> 19:45.950
Where's my daughter?
-You know what? She's not here.

19:45.952 --> 19:47.185
And, to be honest,
I don't really want

19:47.187 --> 19:48.787
To get into this
with you, so --

19:48.788 --> 19:50.388
Well, neither do I, but you're
hiding my daughter, so --

19:50.390 --> 19:52.323
I'm sorry. She is free to go
whenever she wants to.

19:52.325 --> 19:53.925
-Why are you doing this?
-I'm your daughter's friend,

19:53.927 --> 19:55.293
And that is exactly
what she needs right now.

19:55.294 --> 19:56.660
If you were her friend,
you would encourage her

19:56.663 --> 19:58.729
To come home
and sort this out.

19:58.731 --> 20:00.464
To a controlling mother
and a crazy father?

20:00.466 --> 20:02.600
-Excuse me?
-Look, I've been there, okay?

20:02.602 --> 20:04.335
And I'm not gonna
let maddie's opportunities

20:04.337 --> 20:05.820
Slip away from her,
like they did for me.

20:05.821 --> 20:07.304
I care about her too much
to let that happen.

20:07.307 --> 20:09.540
Oh, sweetheart,
you don't care about her at all.

20:09.542 --> 20:10.942
You care about<i> yourself.</i>

20:10.944 --> 20:12.710
And let me tell you
one thing --

20:12.712 --> 20:14.979
Nashville
is such a small town.

20:14.981 --> 20:16.581
If you keep going
down this road,

20:16.583 --> 20:19.517
I guarantee you
I will make sure that no one --

20:19.519 --> 20:22.420
From music row to lower broad --
ever works with you again.

20:22.422 --> 20:24.355
You threatening me?

20:24.357 --> 20:25.790
Promising.

20:31.764 --> 20:34.298
So, out of nowhere,
deacon just storms in,

20:34.300 --> 20:35.900
Starts threatening
this drunk guy,

20:35.902 --> 20:37.235
And pulls me offstage.

20:37.237 --> 20:39.437
At a club, okay?
It was at a club.

20:39.439 --> 20:41.472
I don't know. I might have done
the same thing.

20:41.474 --> 20:42.707
No, you wouldn't have.

20:42.709 --> 20:45.276
You have always
supported my dreams.

20:45.278 --> 20:46.577
I mean, you signed me
to edgehill, right?

20:47.914 --> 20:49.614
Listen,
all you have to do is

20:49.615 --> 20:51.315
Just sign this letter of consent
the lawyers typed up,

20:51.317 --> 20:52.850
And then I can
give it to the judge.

20:52.852 --> 20:57.722
I didn't sign you to edgehill
because I thought it was...

20:57.724 --> 20:59.357
Because I thought it was
the right thing.

20:59.359 --> 21:00.658
What -- what do you mean?

21:00.660 --> 21:01.892
I mean, I was...

21:03.563 --> 21:05.630
I was being blackmailed
by jeff fordham.

21:05.632 --> 21:07.331
But, thankfully,
your mother intervened

21:07.333 --> 21:08.466
And she shut it down.

21:08.468 --> 21:09.900
Why would he
be blackmailing you?

21:11.504 --> 21:14.405
Jeff was threatening
to...

21:14.407 --> 21:16.641
Expose some details
about my personal life.

21:16.643 --> 21:17.908
Like what?

21:17.910 --> 21:20.611
There was a woman
that I was...

21:22.582 --> 21:23.948
...Was involved with.

21:25.051 --> 21:26.550
Oh, my god.

21:26.552 --> 21:28.519
I'm sorry.

21:28.521 --> 21:31.022
I never wanted you to know,
but you have to understand

21:31.024 --> 21:33.557
That your mother has always had
your best interests at heart.

21:33.559 --> 21:34.492
Always.

21:38.931 --> 21:40.998
[ voice breaking ]
so, all my parents
are liars, then.

21:43.436 --> 21:44.769
Maddie.

21:44.771 --> 21:46.304
[ buzzer, door opens ]

21:52.011 --> 21:53.277
Luke, correct me
if I'm wrong here,

21:53.278 --> 21:54.544
But didn't you originally
drop will from your label?

21:54.547 --> 21:56.647
Yeah, I-I did.

21:56.648 --> 21:58.748
Uh, I guess I got a little too
concerned, uh, about my image.

21:58.751 --> 22:00.351
I'm not proud of it,

22:00.353 --> 22:02.053
But, luckily,
I came to my senses.

22:02.055 --> 22:03.521
Will,
how'd that make you feel?

22:03.523 --> 22:04.889
It was rough.

22:04.891 --> 22:06.524
But I understand
why luke did what he did.

22:06.526 --> 22:09.460
It's risky enough
breaking a new artist, but...

22:09.462 --> 22:11.862
A gay artist
in mainstream country --

22:11.864 --> 22:13.497
Felt impossible.

22:13.499 --> 22:16.367
Now, with a label head like him
having my back,

22:16.369 --> 22:18.536
I'm hoping to keep
singing the songs I've sung

22:18.538 --> 22:20.037
Since I was a kid in texas.
-That's right.

22:20.039 --> 22:22.373
[ cheers and applause ]
[ chuckles ]

22:22.375 --> 22:25.409
I have to say, judging by
what we heard earlier,

22:25.411 --> 22:27.111
You're well on your way.

22:27.112 --> 22:28.812
Well, uh,
if you want to hear it again,

22:28.815 --> 22:30.414
That is gonna be
a little tricky.

22:30.416 --> 22:31.883
Why is that?

22:31.884 --> 22:33.351
It seems that some people
aren't gonna be into

22:33.353 --> 22:35.386
Playing an openly gay artist
on the radio.

22:35.388 --> 22:37.421
[ audience jeers ]
wait a minute.

22:37.423 --> 22:39.123
They didn't have a problem
playing him before he came out.

22:39.125 --> 22:41.459
Yeah, that's exactly right,
but, uh,

22:41.461 --> 22:43.661
Now radio programmers are scared
they're gonna get calls

22:43.663 --> 22:48.833
From, uh, a small but loud group
of angry, intolerant haters

22:48.835 --> 22:50.652
If they give will
some airplay.

22:50.653 --> 22:52.470
But y'all heard his single,
right? It's pretty damn good?

22:52.472 --> 22:54.138
[ cheers and applause ]

22:54.140 --> 22:56.907
Well, if your viewers at home
liked what they heard,

22:56.909 --> 22:58.776
They need to call
their local radio stations

22:58.778 --> 23:00.378
And request will's song.

23:00.380 --> 23:02.613
We got to get this boy
played on country radio.

23:02.615 --> 23:05.783
[ cheers and applause ]

23:05.785 --> 23:07.718
[ chuckles ]

23:07.720 --> 23:08.819
[ imitates crowd cheering ]

23:08.821 --> 23:10.488
The crowd goes wild.
[ chuckles ]

23:10.490 --> 23:11.655
That is perfect.

23:11.657 --> 23:13.391
I'm telling you,
you work that hard,

23:13.393 --> 23:16.527
You will be able to play solo
anytime, anywhere.

23:16.529 --> 23:20.731
Even if I could...
I just don't really want to.

23:22.902 --> 23:24.402
I love
singing with maddie.

23:24.404 --> 23:25.870
I know.

23:25.872 --> 23:27.638
Is she ever gonna
play with me ever again

23:27.640 --> 23:29.607
Or even talk to us?

23:29.609 --> 23:31.108
Yeah, absolutely, hon.
Look, we're just --

23:31.110 --> 23:32.743
Your mama and I
are doing everything we can

23:32.745 --> 23:34.412
To get her home right now,
all right?

23:34.414 --> 23:36.947
I don't get
why she's doing this.

23:36.949 --> 23:38.883
I don't, either.

23:38.885 --> 23:40.017
Sometimes
the people we love,

23:40.019 --> 23:41.519
They do things
we don't understand.

23:42.622 --> 23:44.455
She's not coming tonight,
is she?

23:44.457 --> 23:46.657
I don't know.

23:46.659 --> 23:47.725
But<i> I</i> am.

23:49.896 --> 23:51.762
I'll be there
however you need me.

23:52.565 --> 23:53.631
Come here.

23:53.633 --> 23:55.766
[ sniffles ]

23:55.768 --> 23:58.669
Hey, I only have a minute,
but, um,

23:58.671 --> 24:01.138
I saw maddie,
heard her side of the story.

24:01.140 --> 24:02.206
Teddy, you know
she's gonna just say

24:02.208 --> 24:03.941
Exactly what
she wants you to hear.

24:03.943 --> 24:05.643
I'll sign the affidavit,
okay?

24:05.645 --> 24:07.478
I think what she's doing
is absolutely crazy.

24:07.480 --> 24:09.713
I just wish I could
appear in court to say so.

24:09.715 --> 24:11.882
[ sighs ] thank you.

24:11.884 --> 24:13.117
I'm still not convinced

24:13.119 --> 24:14.819
That this whole court thing
has to happen.

24:14.821 --> 24:17.621
If I could just get through
to her face-to-face, you know?

24:17.623 --> 24:19.156
I tried to.

24:19.158 --> 24:22.493
I told her about edgehill --
everything.

24:22.495 --> 24:26.497
I was hoping it would
steer her back to you, but...

24:26.499 --> 24:28.499
She just got up and left.

24:28.501 --> 24:29.800
How long ago
did she leave?

24:29.802 --> 24:32.670
About 20 minutes ago.
Why?

24:32.672 --> 24:34.805
[ mid-tempo music plays ]

24:34.807 --> 24:36.507
You think, uh,
since we're stuck here,

24:36.509 --> 24:38.509
We should try to prepare
for tomorrow or something?

24:38.511 --> 24:39.543
Scarlett, we've been
doing interviews

24:39.545 --> 24:40.678
For four days straight.

24:40.680 --> 24:41.712
You really think
we need to practice?

24:41.714 --> 24:43.214
It's<i> rolling stone.</i>

24:43.216 --> 24:44.815
It's just gonna be the same
as all the others.

24:44.817 --> 24:46.050
They're gonna ask
the same questions.

24:46.052 --> 24:47.952
"are you really exes?"
"yes."

24:47.954 --> 24:49.520
"who are
your musical influences?"

24:49.522 --> 24:50.921
"james taylor."
"autumn chase."

24:50.923 --> 24:52.756
I'm changing my answer
to that one.

24:52.758 --> 24:55.659
"where did you two first meet?"
"working at the bluebird."

24:55.661 --> 24:59.530
You know, you keep saying that,
but it's not where we first met.

24:59.532 --> 25:00.931
We first met

25:00.933 --> 25:03.033
At a street fair you were
playing in east nashville

25:03.035 --> 25:04.935
With that little rockabilly trio
you used to have.

25:04.937 --> 25:07.905
I went up after your set,
introduced myself,

25:07.907 --> 25:08.973
And, uh, said
I really liked your music,

25:08.975 --> 25:11.275
And you were real nice.

25:11.276 --> 25:13.576
You welcomed me to nashville,
and, um...

25:13.579 --> 25:15.046
That was it.

25:15.047 --> 25:16.514
How come you never
told me that before?

25:16.516 --> 25:17.715
I didn't expect you
to remember.

25:17.717 --> 25:19.617
I was just a face in the crowd
that day.

25:19.619 --> 25:20.951
Nobody special.

25:20.953 --> 25:22.586
You remembered<i> me.</i>

25:22.587 --> 25:24.220
Well, that's 'cause you were
the only boy I ever heard

25:24.223 --> 25:26.123
Sing as high as me.
-[ chuckles ] nice.

25:26.125 --> 25:27.725
Thanks a lot.

25:34.934 --> 25:36.800
Rest up for tomorrow,
okay?

25:36.802 --> 25:38.202
Yeah, I will.
Thanks.

25:48.180 --> 25:49.680
Maddie!

25:51.751 --> 25:54.285
Maddie,
please just talk to me.

25:54.287 --> 25:57.087
[ voice breaking ]
why didn't you tell me?

25:57.089 --> 25:59.189
About edgehill,
about my dad?

25:59.191 --> 26:01.959
Because it's my job
as your mother

26:01.961 --> 26:04.228
To protect you from things
that are gonna break your heart.

26:04.230 --> 26:06.030
Like what?! The truth?!

26:06.032 --> 26:07.598
You just --
you kept it from me!

26:07.600 --> 26:09.083
Yes, I did.

26:09.084 --> 26:10.567
I had other label offers
after edgehill,

26:10.570 --> 26:12.036
But you signed me
to this fake deal

26:12.038 --> 26:13.671
Only so you could
control me!

26:13.673 --> 26:14.905
That's not true at all.

26:14.907 --> 26:18.075
This deal is
absolutely real for you.

26:18.077 --> 26:20.277
Just as my belief in you
as an artist is.

26:20.279 --> 26:23.881
Honey, I want to support you
and I want to build you.

26:23.883 --> 26:26.817
And I don't want you
to be exploited.

26:26.819 --> 26:29.353
You know that's true.
You have to believe that's true.

26:29.355 --> 26:32.089
I honestly don't know
what to believe anymore.

26:32.091 --> 26:35.626
Well, believe in us.
Believe in your family.

26:35.628 --> 26:38.028
We've always been able to
get through everything together.

26:38.030 --> 26:40.664
Everything
is already in motion.

26:40.666 --> 26:42.032
Says who?

26:42.034 --> 26:45.736
Says cash?
Says the lawyer?

26:45.738 --> 26:48.105
Honey, listen to your heart.
Is this what you want?

26:48.107 --> 26:49.974
I just need to think.

26:49.976 --> 26:52.176
Well, think.

26:52.178 --> 26:55.012
But don't do it
at some hearing.

26:55.014 --> 26:57.781
Don't let some court
and some lawyer

26:57.783 --> 27:00.084
Decide how you want
your life to be.

27:02.822 --> 27:04.688
I should go inside.

27:04.690 --> 27:06.056
Please come home.

27:12.365 --> 27:13.631
[ sighs ]

27:13.633 --> 27:15.299
[ knock on door ]

27:15.301 --> 27:17.301
I told you I needed to see you
hours ago,

27:17.303 --> 27:19.070
And you're just now
showing up?

27:19.071 --> 27:20.838
I told you I had to go
to juliette's rehearsal.

27:20.840 --> 27:22.139
What do you need?

27:22.141 --> 27:24.208
To be your priority,
like you promised.

27:24.210 --> 27:25.976
You told me not to worry when
you took her back as a client

27:25.978 --> 27:27.678
Because she was inactive,

27:27.680 --> 27:29.647
But -- surprise, surprise --
juliette's joined my tour.

27:29.649 --> 27:31.649
[ scoffs ] I was just
as blindsided as<i> you</i> were.

27:31.651 --> 27:32.816
Uh-huh.

27:32.818 --> 27:34.051
Look, you also told me
not to worry

27:34.053 --> 27:35.886
Because I would be
your priority,

27:35.888 --> 27:37.655
But, lo and behold, you've been
at her beck and call

27:37.657 --> 27:38.956
Since she got here.

27:38.958 --> 27:41.025
[ sighs ]
okay, look.

27:41.027 --> 27:44.094
You're -- you're focusing on
all the wrong things right here.

27:44.096 --> 27:46.063
Yes, she's keeping me busier
than I'd like,

27:46.065 --> 27:47.965
But juliette being on this tour
with you is a great thing.

27:47.967 --> 27:50.100
[ scoffs ]
how do you figure that?

27:50.102 --> 27:52.102
You have this huge
audience overlap with her

27:52.104 --> 27:54.104
That you don't have
with luke wheeler.

27:54.106 --> 27:56.206
Your performance last night
was terrific.

27:56.208 --> 27:58.142
Your show's running
flawlessly.

27:58.144 --> 27:59.943
Bucky loves the rough cut
of the video.

27:59.945 --> 28:01.311
-Really?
-Yeah.

28:01.313 --> 28:02.813
He loves it?

28:02.815 --> 28:04.314
Rayna's gonna love it, too.

28:04.316 --> 28:08.085
My point is,
everything is coming up layla.

28:08.087 --> 28:10.454
And juliette is
absolutely no threat to you.

28:12.725 --> 28:15.926
Uh...
Cadence is napping, so...

28:15.928 --> 28:18.128
I just wanted
to talk to you.

28:18.130 --> 28:19.830
Okay.

28:25.071 --> 28:27.304
Look, I wasn't completely honest
this morning.

28:27.306 --> 28:29.406
Glenn --

28:29.408 --> 28:31.375
It wasn't his idea
for you to play "dirt" with me.

28:31.377 --> 28:32.342
It was mine.

28:32.344 --> 28:33.410
Oh. Okay.

28:33.412 --> 28:36.046
Well, um...

28:36.048 --> 28:37.414
The answer's still "no."

28:37.416 --> 28:39.483
Avery, I...

28:39.485 --> 28:42.286
I don't want to lie to you
anymore.

28:42.288 --> 28:44.955
I want to be honest with you
about how I'm feeling.

28:47.460 --> 28:49.460
I still love you.

28:49.462 --> 28:50.461
Juliette --

28:50.463 --> 28:52.096
And I know
that you love me.

28:52.098 --> 28:54.131
Don't do this.
Deep down,
beneath all the anger --

28:54.133 --> 28:56.467
This is not
going to work.

28:56.469 --> 28:57.768
It<i> will</i> work.

28:57.770 --> 28:59.336
It<i> can</i> work.

28:59.338 --> 29:01.071
Because I know
what's in there.

29:01.073 --> 29:02.473
I know
that it's in your heart.

29:02.475 --> 29:04.174
Yes, of course it is.

29:04.176 --> 29:07.044
Of course it's there,
because what we had was real.

29:07.046 --> 29:10.080
What I gave you of myself
was real.

29:11.250 --> 29:13.183
And I hate it now.

29:13.185 --> 29:15.252
I hate the fact
that you're here,

29:15.254 --> 29:17.488
Because all I want to do
is get on with my life,

29:17.490 --> 29:19.923
Because what you do to me
is what you did,

29:19.925 --> 29:21.058
And you're gonna
do it again!

29:21.060 --> 29:24.995
I am so sorry
that I hurt you.

29:24.997 --> 29:27.931
And I destroyed
everything,

29:27.933 --> 29:29.900
And I-I can't do anything
about it.

29:29.902 --> 29:31.401
I can't undo it.

29:31.403 --> 29:34.505
All I can do is promise you
that I am different.

29:34.507 --> 29:38.342
And if we work together,
we could rebuild what we had.

29:38.344 --> 29:41.545
And it will be better
than it was before.

29:41.547 --> 29:43.347
[ cadence fusses ]

29:43.349 --> 29:44.982
[ sighs ]

29:47.286 --> 29:49.453
I have to
take care of cadence.

29:51.824 --> 29:53.557
You don't have to
answer now.

29:53.559 --> 29:57.227
You just take your time.

29:57.229 --> 30:01.265
And when you make your decision,
you know where to find me.

30:05.871 --> 30:07.971
[ cadence crying ]

30:17.950 --> 30:19.883
[ door closes ]

30:19.885 --> 30:20.551
[ sighs ]

30:26.058 --> 30:27.391
Hey, mike.
Hey, deacon.

30:27.393 --> 30:29.092
Thank you for your help.

30:29.094 --> 30:30.828
You mind grabbing this stuff
for me?

30:30.830 --> 30:32.262
Here's some lights here
for you.

30:32.264 --> 30:34.081
All right,
thank you, guys.

30:34.082 --> 30:35.899
Paul, I'm gonna take that one,
actually. That's my daughter's.

30:35.901 --> 30:37.601
Okay.
I appreciate it.

30:39.104 --> 30:41.038
Hey.
-Hey.

30:41.040 --> 30:42.439
Daphne's up getting ready.

30:42.441 --> 30:43.507
Okay.

30:44.844 --> 30:46.143
You got to see maddie,
talk with her?

30:46.145 --> 30:47.377
-Yeah. Yeah.
-How'd it go?

30:47.379 --> 30:49.213
I don't know if I got through
to her or not.

30:49.215 --> 30:50.514
You think
she's gonna come?

30:50.516 --> 30:52.316
We'll see.

30:52.318 --> 30:54.284
All right, well, at least
you made contact, right?

30:54.286 --> 30:56.687
Yeah.

30:56.688 --> 30:59.089
And if she doesn't make it,
daphne's ready, all right?

30:59.091 --> 31:01.091
We had
a one-on-one guitar lesson,

31:01.093 --> 31:02.993
And, uh,
she's doing great.

31:02.995 --> 31:05.028
I know. I heard.

31:05.030 --> 31:06.096
Thank you.

31:08.200 --> 31:09.266
Let's go get dressed.

31:09.268 --> 31:10.934
Let's go.

31:10.936 --> 31:13.003
[ door closes ]

31:13.005 --> 31:14.438
Hey, so, I talked
to your lawyer.

31:14.440 --> 31:16.940
Don't even worry about your dad
siding with your mom.

31:16.942 --> 31:19.309
We still have
a really strong case.

31:19.311 --> 31:21.378
Do you think that maybe
I've just taken this too far?

31:21.380 --> 31:23.864
Maddie, no.

31:23.865 --> 31:26.349
We've got offers coming in
from all over -- new york, l.A.

31:26.352 --> 31:28.552
You're gonna have
a serious career.

31:28.554 --> 31:30.888
I was just supposed
to play this benefit
with my sister tonight.

31:30.890 --> 31:32.890
She's, like,
really upset about it,

31:32.892 --> 31:34.958
And I can't even
text her back.

31:34.960 --> 31:37.294
Hey, remember what
the lawyer said, though.

31:37.296 --> 31:39.162
I mean, that could be
your mom texting you.

31:39.999 --> 31:41.298
I talked to her,
you know.

31:41.300 --> 31:42.633
When?

31:42.635 --> 31:44.601
When you were in meetings.

31:44.603 --> 31:46.570
She said she wanted to try
and work it out.

31:49.174 --> 31:51.541
Well, guess what
your mom said to<i> me.</i>

31:53.379 --> 31:55.545
Got to say, you handled yourself
like a pro.

31:55.547 --> 31:57.614
Big day, big audience.

31:57.616 --> 31:59.383
You rose to the occasion.

31:59.385 --> 32:01.485
Thanks for having my back, luke.
I appreciate it.

32:01.487 --> 32:02.986
You got it, son.
Now let's get back home.

32:04.690 --> 32:06.256
[ sighs ]

32:09.461 --> 32:11.261
Don't give me that look.

32:11.263 --> 32:13.330
You ask me,
that was a hell of a launch.

32:13.332 --> 32:14.598
Sure --
except for the part

32:14.600 --> 32:16.967
Where you called out
country radio on national tv.

32:16.969 --> 32:18.535
[ chuckling ] I wish
you hadn't have done that.

32:18.537 --> 32:20.170
Yeah, well,
now they have no choice

32:20.172 --> 32:21.939
But to give the man
some airplay

32:21.941 --> 32:23.440
When listeners
request his song.

32:23.442 --> 32:25.042
Maybe.

32:25.044 --> 32:26.443
Maybe make some enemies,
too.

32:26.445 --> 32:29.112
Oh, smile, kenneth.
It's gonna be great.

32:29.114 --> 32:31.615
Probably -- for will.
He's got nothing to lose.

32:31.617 --> 32:33.517
Unlike<i> you.</i>

